# A/B Testing - Multi-Armed Bandit

## Overview
This project implements two Multi-Armed Bandit strategies for A/B testing:
- Epsilon-Greedy with decaying epsilon (e = 1/t)
- Thompson Sampling with known precision (Gaussian conjugate prior)

Four advertisement bandits are tested with true mean rewards of [1, 2, 3, 4] over 20,000 trials.

## Setup
Install dependencies:

    pip install -r requirements.txt

## Run

    python Bandit.py

## Output
- results.csv - rewards per trial (columns: Bandit, Reward, Algorithm)
- plot1_learning_curves.png - learning process for each algorithm
- plot2_comparison.png - cumulative rewards and regrets comparison

## Project Structure
- Bandit.py
- requirements.txt
- README.md

## Results
- Epsilon-Greedy cumulative reward: ~79843
- Epsilon-Greedy cumulative regret: ~156
- Thompson Sampling cumulative reward: ~80105
- Thompson Sampling cumulative regret: ~-105

Thompson Sampling converges faster to the optimal bandit.